Feature: Multiple metatype observers on same event
Description: Verify that multiple metatype bindings (Profile/Transition) can observe the same event
Acceptance Criteria:
  - Multiple metatype bindings should each get unique synthetic variable names
  - Both observers should fire on event completion
  - Continuation code should have access to metatype binding variables
Known Issue:
  - When multiple metatype_binding steps of the same type are emitted,
    they currently get the same synthetic name (e.g., _profile_47182).
    The tap transformer or emitter needs to use a counter to make unique names.
  - This manifests as "undeclared identifier" errors in the generated backend code
